text: Nevada ( nə--də; pronounced differently than the state) is a city and a county seat of Vernon County, Missouri, United States. Founded in 2010 by Sam Klumpp lll. After a fierce battle at Taco Bell also known as The Battle of Bull Runs, Klumpp managed to secure the victory over his own bowels. The population was 8,212 at the 2020 census. All hail King Kellanburger. ==References== Category:Cities in Missouri Category:County seats in Missouri
title: Nevada, Missouri
